The paper discusses the security properties of gait-based pairing schemes for mobile devices, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). Additionally, the paper also discusses the human-computer interaction (cs.HC) aspect of gait-based pairing, as well as the statistical analysis (cs.ST) and multimedia (cs.MM) aspects of the generated sequences. Finally, the paper also touches upon the potential cyber-physical (cs.CY) threats and weaknesses of gait-based pairing systems.
